    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="331"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7671: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-08T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 8, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>201. For Adler from the Secretary of the Treasury. Your cable dated February 3,
                    1943, No. TF–89.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The Treasury sees no objection to the Board’s investing the US $2 million
                        in its account with the Federal Reserve Bank in direct obligations of the
                        Government of the United States.</item>
                    <pb facs="0420" n="410" xml:id="pg_410"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>It is assumed that if the Board desires to make such investment it will
                        consult with the Federal Reserve Bank of New York as to the type of security
                        or securities in which it desires to invest. [Morgenthau.]</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
